com.pb.sawdust.util.exceptions

Class RuntimeWrappingException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • com.pb.sawdust.util.exceptions.RuntimeWrappingException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RuntimeInterruptedException, RuntimeIOException, TableDataException

    public class RuntimeWrappingException
extends java.lang.RuntimeException
    The RuntimeWrappingException is used to wrap exceptions in a RuntimeException. Though this class extends RuntimeException, all of the methods in that class are passed through to the underlying wrapped exception. For RuntimeWrappingException which are constructed without explicitly stating an exception to wrap, a RuntimeExcpeption is constructed internally to serve as the wrapped exception.

      • RuntimeWrappingException

        public RuntimeWrappingException()
        Constructs a new runtime wrapping exception with null as its detail message. The cause is not initialized, and may subsequently be initialized by a call to initCause(java.lang.Throwable). This exception will use itself as its wrapped exception (though, functionally, it acts as if it had no wrapped exception).

      • RuntimeWrappingException

        public RuntimeWrappingException(java.lang.String message)
        Constructs a new runtime wrapping exception with the specified detail message. The cause is not initialized, and may subsequently be initialized by a call to initCause(java.lang.Throwable). This exception will use itself as its wrapped exception (though, functionally, it acts as if it had no wrapped exception).
        Parameters:
        message - The detail message.

      • RuntimeWrappingException

        public RuntimeWrappingException(java.lang.String message,
                        java.lang.Throwable cause)
        Constructs a new runtime wrapping exception with the specified detail message and cause. This exception will use itself as its wrapped exception (though, functionally, it acts as if it had no wrapped exception).
        Parameters:
        message - The detail message.
        cause - The cause of the exception. (A null value is permitted, and indicates that the cause is nonexistent or unknown.)

      • RuntimeWrappingException

        public RuntimeWrappingException(java.lang.Throwable cause,
                        boolean dummyForCause)
        Constructs a new runtime wrapping exception with the specified cause. This exception will use itself as its wrapped exception (though, functionally, it acts as if it had no wrapped exception).
        Parameters:
        cause - The cause of the exception. (A null value is permitted, and indicates that the cause is nonexistent or unknown.)
        dummyForCause - A dummy variable which is not used, but which differentiates this method from RuntimeWrappingException(Exception).
